{"word":"κραιπνός","slug":"κραιπνός","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>κραιπνός</b></el> <p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>rapid, rushing</i>, of strong winds, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>; of <i>swift</i> feet, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>:—<a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> <i>hasty, rash</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:Adverb'>adv.</a>, <i>quickly, hastily</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>; also <a href='S:neuter'>neut.</a> <a href='S:plural'>pl.</a> as <a href='S:Adverb'>adv.</a>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}